EVACUATION ON WATER
The aircraft is equipped with 25-MAN/
30-MAN LIFE RAFTS, stowed in ceiling
compartments, inside the main cabin.
These compartments, placarded "LIFE
RAFT",
are adjacent to each
EMER-

MAIN
CABIN
ENTRY/EXIT)
DOOR.
ESCAPE ROPES:
Overwing escape ropes are contained in the overhead liferaft compartments adjacent to
doors L3 and R3. The compartments are labeled to identify rope locations.
One end of each rope is permanently secured to the airplane structure. The opposite end is
equipped with a snap fastener. This fastener is pulled out onto the wing and is attached to
a bracket located between the inboard and outboard engines. The rope will aid personnel
in maintaining footing while moving outboard on the wing to the LIFE RAFTS. The rope
level is such that children may grasp it without difficulty, while traversing the wing,
during ditching. These ropes could also be used for emergency land evacuation.

Each 25/30-MAN LIFE RAFT weighs approximately 120 Ibs. and
should be removed from the ceiling compartment by two able-bodied
persons; positioned near an EMERGENCY (MAIN CABIN ENTRY EXIT
DOOR and secured to the aircraft prior to launching.
1. Pull compartment door release latch
and allow door to swing open.
2. Unfasten restraining buckles/straps
secured around LIFE RAFT. Grab WHITE
assist straps on side of LIFE RAFT and
lower to floor. Close ceiling compartment.
WARNING!
DO NOT INFLATE LIFE RAFT
INSIDE AIRCRAFT
A. Position LIFE RAFT at EMERGENCY (MAIN CABIN ENTRY/EXIT) DOOR with RED
flap upward. Unsnap RED flap and secure lanyard snaphook to forward door assist
handle / seat leg / fastened seat belt, or exposed door hinge nearest the EXIT door
threshold, at ALL doors EXCEPT #L4 and #R4. At these doors attach the lanyard to
the aft door assist handle.
Porward dool
B. After opening door, place LIFE RAFT on EXIT door threshold. Grasp inflation han
die and pull hard as you push LIFE RAFT out of aircraft. The initial pull on the infla
tion handle expells the raft from its case; a secondary pull will discharge the infla
tion bottles and the raft will inflate in approximately 15 seconds.
